I've struggled with this as well. I think `host` has been superseded by `connections.incoming.net[].external`, which I think was changed because we may want to do different types of connections per hostname.

```json
{
 "connections": {
    "incoming": {
      "net": [
        {
          "port": 8008,
          "scope": "public",
          "transform": "shs",
          "external": "example.com"
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
```
